v-0.03
🚀 TechBites TweakHub — Release Notes

 🆕 What's New in This Build

⚡ Real-Time System Detection on Startup**
   *Fixed a bug* where the dashboard would show stale toggle states if you made registry or system setting changes outside of the app. TweakHub now runs a fresh, live system scan every time the application boots up.
⚙️ Smarter Registry Value Matching**
*Fixed a bug* where the app would mistakenly report a tweak as "disabled" if Windows used an alternative non-zero value for an enabled feature. Any non-zero DWORD/QWORD value is now correctly read as "enabled" when the target expected value is `1`.
🎛️ New Advanced Multi-Option Dropdowns**
**Alt+Tab Filter**: Converted from a simple toggle to a dropdown. You can now select exactly how many Edge tabs appear in your Alt+Tab view (*Show all tabs*, *5 tabs*, *3 tabs*, or *Windows only*).
**Show Drive Letters**: Converted to a dropdown supporting all four Windows Explorer display modes (*Show after labels*, *Network drives only*, *Hide completely*, or *Show all before labels*).
**💾 Preserved Option Backups & Revert**
*Fixed a bug* where reverting selection-based tweaks would reset them to a generic default state. The app now backs up the exact prior option and restores it perfectly when reverted.
